cluded in Mr. Ehlers amendment.

However,  I  would  like  to  express  my  concern  that  there  are  at  least  28  NOAA
facilities with budgets between $1 and $5 million. NOAA will merely have to notify
Congress  of  closures,  relocations  or  consolidations  of  these  facilities  without  going
through an evaluation process.

I do not believe that we know enough about how this will affect these 28 facilities

at this time to set the number at $5 million.

While  I  do  not  want  to  try  to  amend  this  language  in  an  effort  to  move  the  bill
through  Committee,  I  plan  to  continue  to  work  on  issue  in  an  effort  to  ensure  that
any  changes  to  the  organization  of  NOAA  facilities  is  thoroughly  evaluated  and
